      SOURCE_URL=http://www.kde-apps.org/content/files/
      SOURCE_VFY=sha1:cbf65d2f2caa99eb0bc6ee2cc169eaf2d8a13a31
        WEB_SITE=http://www.kde-apps.org/content/show.php?content=30375/
         ENTERED=20051130
         UPDATED=20051215
           SHORT="decoding library used in akode_artsplugin in kdemultimedia"

cat << EOF
Not really a KDE application and not even an application, but very usefull non
the less.

 aKode is the decoding library used in akode_artsplugin in kdemultimedia, and
 improves the aRts experience by fewer drop-outs, more supported formats and
 fewer bugs in general.

 It can also be used directly without aRts in JuK and Amarok.

 aKode supports decoding of MPEG audio, Ogg Vorbis, Ogg FLAC, old FLAC, Speex,
  WAV, and Musepack audio.

EOF
